author: Russell Brand
description:
Tony Blair is back—and he wants you to carry a digital ID. Russell exposes the UK’s new “Brit Card” scheme, revealing how immigration panic, climate fear, and pandemic memories are being weaponized to justify mass surveillance and total control. With Labour pushing ahead and Starmer embracing Blair’s globalist playbook, is this the most dangerous policy since the poll tax? From centralized IDs to biometric tracking, Russell lays out how technocratic tyranny is creeping in—and how we can resist.
